{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/notes/css-blur-effect/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"CSS blur effect","date":"2016-10-25T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"October 25th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","last_modified_at":"2016-11-04T20:13:05.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"4 years ago","path":"/notes/css-blur-effect/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"tags":["TIL","web development"],"image":null,"toc":null,"comments":null,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"a064052d-a333-591d-9a92-c8b127deae19","html":"<p>Playing with the new <strong>Depth Effect</strong> (aka <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/fauxkeh/\"><em>fauxkeh</em></a>) on my iPhone 7 Plus got me thinking about Gaussian blurs, and how to improve their use on this site.</p>\n<p>In this <a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-jekyll/tree/11.0.0\">last redesign</a>, I applied a blurred effect to images in a few key locations<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup>. To keep page speed in check I shrunk images down to <code class=\"language-text\">~20px</code> wide, optimized them with <a href=\"https://github.com/imagemin/imagemin\"><strong>imagemin</strong></a>, and then scaled them up with <code class=\"language-text\">background-size: cover</code> to fill their parent containers.</p>\n<p>The browser does the rest, enlarging and smoothing out these tiny images — creating a blurred effect of sorts. For the most part they look good. On devices that display <code class=\"language-text\">@2x</code> or higher, blotchy patterns and artifacts begin to show their ugly faces.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26.545454545454543%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"ugly upscaled images on a high resolution display\"\n        title=\"ugly upscaled images on a high resolution display\"\n        data-src=\"/static/f87759c53fe31b556eb5347a27c7b6b1/eacc7/mm-upscaled-image-blur-ipad.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/f87759c53fe31b556eb5347a27c7b6b1/16841/mm-upscaled-image-blur-ipad.jpg 275w,\n/static/f87759c53fe31b556eb5347a27c7b6b1/50c97/mm-upscaled-image-blur-ipad.jpg 550w,\n/static/f87759c53fe31b556eb5347a27c7b6b1/eacc7/mm-upscaled-image-blur-ipad.jpg 1100w,\n/static/f87759c53fe31b556eb5347a27c7b6b1/490e5/mm-upscaled-image-blur-ipad.jpg 1600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is where <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/almanac/properties/f/filter/\">CSS filter functions</a> like <code class=\"language-text\">blur</code> come into play. By adding a single line to my stylesheet I was able to smoothen out these images just enough to overcome the ugly.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"diff\"><pre class=\"language-diff\"><code class=\"language-diff\">.teaser__bg {\n<span class=\"token unchanged\">  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  right: 0;\n  bottom: 0;\n  left: 0;\n</span><span class=\"token inserted-sign inserted\">+ filter: blur(15px);\n</span><span class=\"token unchanged\">  background-repeat: no-repeat;\n  background-size: cover;\n</span>}</code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32.72727272727273%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"blur filtered background images\"\n        title=\"blur filtered background images\"\n        data-src=\"/static/7fffd61dff2c0a7916739d0e0c2f6a1c/eacc7/mm-image-filter-blur-ipad-1124.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/7fffd61dff2c0a7916739d0e0c2f6a1c/16841/mm-image-filter-blur-ipad-1124.jpg 275w,\n/static/7fffd61dff2c0a7916739d0e0c2f6a1c/50c97/mm-image-filter-blur-ipad-1124.jpg 550w,\n/static/7fffd61dff2c0a7916739d0e0c2f6a1c/eacc7/mm-image-filter-blur-ipad-1124.jpg 1100w,\n/static/7fffd61dff2c0a7916739d0e0c2f6a1c/c9069/mm-image-filter-blur-ipad-1124.jpg 1124w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>The best part, browser <a href=\"http://caniuse.com/#search=filter\">support for CSS filter effects</a> is quite good.</p>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p><strong>Cover images</strong> with a striped pattern overlay. <strong>Background images</strong> in the post pagination links found at the bottom of each page.</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","excerpt":"Playing with the new Depth Effect (aka fauxkeh) on my iPhone 7 Plus got me thinking about Gaussian blurs, and how to improve their use on…","timeToRead":1,"tableOfContents":""},"comments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/notes/oil-pastels/","title":"Oil pastels are not pencils","categories":["notes"],"tags":["TIL","illustration"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/notes/oil-pastels.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/notes/using-ssi/","title":"Using SSI to detect cookies","categories":["notes"],"tags":["TIL","web development","Jekyll"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/notes/using-ssi.md"}}}}